Step-by-step reasoning:
- The user wants to turn on the Kitchen_mid_front light to 75% brightness.
- The ramp rate should be fast, so we choose a short ramp rate enum value, for example 0.1 seconds (enum 31).
- The trigger condition is when Rear_outside light is turned on physically, which is a COC event with command Fast On [DFON].
- We check for Rear_outside device sending command DFON.
- The action sequence is to set Kitchen_mid_front ramp rate to 0.1 seconds, then turn it on with 75% brightness.
- Commands to use:
  - Ramp Rate [RR] with parameter 31 (0.1 seconds)
  - On [DON] with parameter 75 (75%)

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn on Kitchen_mid_front fast when Rear_outside physically turned on",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "Rear_outside",
        "coc": "DFON"
      }
    },
    "actions": [
      {
        "device": "Kitchen_mid_front",
        "command": "RR",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "Ramp Rate", "value": 31, "uom": "enum", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "Kitchen_mid_front",
        "command": "DON",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "On Level", "value": 75, "uom": "%", "precision": 1 }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
